watched.title: Climate Change - by Chris Riedy
watched.copy: In the period since the Industrial Revolution, human emissions of greenhouse gases from fossil fuel combustion, deforestation and agricultural practices have led to global warming and climate change.

watched.title: Living Planet: Water wars
watched.copy: In the Global North, clean water is taken for granted — but in some places it means the difference between life and death. "Water wars" are taking place as people fight failing systems, and combat climate change, to access enough clean water for all.

watched.title: Triggered - CNN's Climate Propaganda Night
watched.copy: Last night was CNN's climate propaganda night. The top 10 Democratic candidates headed into an echo chamber to discuss their radical climate change policies. Matt and Storm discuss.

watched.title: A spike in Arctic lightning strikes may be linked to climate change
watched.copy: Arctic lightning has gotten way more frequent over the last decade amid rising global temperatures, study finds

watched.title: The New Face Of Climate Change — The Climate Migrant
watched.copy: 4 min (VICE) report on potential climate refugees/migrants in mexico

watched.title: Do 97% of scientists actually agree on climate change?
watched.copy: 3 min (OAN) interview with climate change skeptics, arguing that not all scientists argee and that consensus may not be correct

watched.title:
Under-reporting of greenhouse gas emissions
in U.S. cities
watched.copy:
Cities dominate greenhouse gas emissions. Many have generated self-reported emission
inventories, but their value to emissions mitigation depends on their accuracy, which remains
untested.
